      "note_no": "9",
      "note": "I.e., in the words of Razi, \"towards self-surrender to God's will ..., [and so] towards gratitude in times of ease, and patience in times of misfortune\". It is also possible - as some of the commentators do - to understand the phrase in another sense, namely, \"if anyone believes in God, He [i.e., God] guides his heart\". However, the rendering adopted by me seems to be preferable inasmuch as it stresses the idea that conscious belief in God impels a man's reason to control and direct his emotions and inclinations in accordance with all that this belief implies."
